data.enText: only present in small amounts or numbers and often spread over a large area
the sparse population of the islands

data.chText: 山上越高的地方植物越稀少。
data.enText: Vegetation becomes sparse higher up the mountains.
The information available on the subject is sparse.

value.def: Something that is sparse is small in number or amount and spread out over an area.

example.ex: Many slopes are rock fields with sparse vegetation...
example.tran: 许多山坡都是石头地，植被稀疏。

example.ex: He was a tubby little man in his fifties, with sparse hair...
example.tran: 他50来岁，头发稀疏，身材矮胖。

example.ex: Traffic was sparse on the highway.
...the sparsely populated interior region, where there are few roads.
example.tran: 人口分散、公路稀少的内地
